
GIT

Install git on ubuntu
 
	sudo apt-get install git
	
Get git version
	
	git --version
	
Set user-name on local git
	
	git config --global user.name joshi-tarun
	
Get username on local gir
	
	git config --global user.name
	
	
Set email on local git
	
	git config --global user.email tarun.joshi@tworoads-trading.co.in
	
Get email on local git
	
	git config --global user.email
	
Directly make changes on the configuration file
	
	git config --global --edit
	
	
Git Repository is a project/folder which is monitored or tracked with the help of git software

Initalize a folder to git
	
	git init

Status of a file
	
	git status
	
	Status can be untracked, Unmodified, Modified, Staging area
	

Change status of a file from untracked to track (Staging area)

	git add index.html
	
 
Save Current file structure / Inital commit


	git commit -m "First Commit"
	
	First commit also store the message with this commit
	

Create a file with the help of terminal

	touch name.html
	
To track all the untracked/modified files at once and move them to staging area
	
	git track -A
	git add .
	

To commit again skipping the use of VIM editor

	git commit -m "Commit Message"

To retrive the last committed file after multiple changes had been made

	git checkout contact.html
	
	git checkout (Hashcode of the commit from git log)
	
	git checkout master 	
	  	
To retrive the last committed folder after multiple changes had been made

	git checkout -f
	

To check all the commits


	git log
	

To check only last n (n = 5) commits
	
	git log -p -n
	git log -p -5
	
To print the changes in the orginal file and modified file

	git diff
	
Directly commit skipping ataging area

	git commit -a -m "Skipped staging area"
	

Delete file from everwhere 
	
	git rm contact.html
	

Short status of a reposistry

	git status -s
	




Master Branch

Create a new branch from existing master branch

	git branch feature1  // feature1 is the branch name


Check current branch
	
	git branch

Change to another directory

	git checkout feature1


Merge feature1 branch with Master branch

	git merger feature1

Create an directly take to the newely created branch

	git checkout -b feature2
	

Create a gitignore file

	touch .gitignore
	
	Now add all the required file in .gitignore file
	
	gitignore file can also be added inside gitignore file to avoid tracking 
	
	


